<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">First-time withdrawals sometimes need manual approval as well, especially in the case of a new deposit. In this case, the checking aims to verify your identity and the source of your funding. Substantial amounts in withdrawals will be verified, too, especially if they exceed certain thresholds. The administrators will have a look into that every time, whether you’ve performed a transaction like that in the past or not. If your ID verification is still pending, the withdrawal could be processed via manual approval as well after the documentation has been validated.</span></p>
