					<description><![CDATA[<p>Reserv has secured a $125 million Series C investment. Facilitated by global investment corporation KKR in a Series C financing, the investment represents a major move for the New York-based</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/reserv-raises-125m-to-transform-insurance-claims/" data-wpel-link="internal">Reserv Raises $125M to Transform Insurance Claims</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.reserv.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Reserv </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has secured a $125 million Series C </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/axoft-raises-55m-to-transform-brain-machine-tech/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">investment</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Facilitated by global investment corporation KKR in a Series C financing, the investment represents a major move for the New York-based business as it replaces its legacy systems with an AI-native third-party administrator solution.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Existing investors Bain Capital Ventures and Flourish Ventures, and a handful of strategic insurance partners and customers, joined the round. The new investment reflects the tremendous growth Reserv has experienced, reaching $100m of ARR a mere four years after inception.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Legacy Obstacle</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Established in 2022 by CJ Przybyl (previously Snapsheet CSO) and Martha Dreiling (formerly an executive at Rhino and OnDeck), Reserv was born from a straightforward principle: insurance claims take too long because the tech to facilitate them is outdated. Conventional TPAs often necessitate manual data entry and disconnected tools, resulting in substantial delays for consumers and increased costs of serving them.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We started this company to prove how seamless claims processing could be if technology wasn&#8217;t the obstacle,&#8221; said CEO CJ Przybyl. &#8220;Our focus is not just on building tools for adjusters but on the automation of the entire organisation. We’ve reached a scale where we can now automate even the most complex commercial claims.&#8221;</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200547" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200547" class="size-full wp-image-200547" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Reserv_Wordmark_Dark_Green.jpg" alt="Reserv Logo" width="480" height="130" /><p id="caption-attachment-200547" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Reserv</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Reserv’s flagship platform, Reserv Glance&#x2122;, allows insurers and brokers to migrate entire databases of historical and open claims into a centralised, AI-driven environment. By utilising &#8220;explainable AI&#8221;, the platform can analyse claims data, flag anomalies, and automate workflows in a matter of weeks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/axoft-raises-55m-to-transform-brain-machine-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Axoft Raises $55M to Transform Brain-Machine Tech</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Ambitious Targets: 30 Million Claims</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The scale of Reserv’s ambition is reflected in its roadmap. The company currently employs over 500 claims adjusters and has the capacity to handle approximately 500,000 complex claims. claims annually. With the $125 million infusion, Reserv plans to more than double its capacity every year, targeting a staggering 30 million annual claims within the next four years.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This expansion is specifically aimed at the Property and Casualty (P&amp;C) sector, focusing on non-field-based commercial claims. This massive market has historically been resistant to full automation due to its complexity.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Institutional Vote of Confidence</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For KKR, the investment is a strategic bet on the digital transformation of the insurance value chain. The investment was made primarily through KKR’s Next Generation Technology Growth strategy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;What Reserv has done from an AI and operational perspective is truly differentiated,&#8221; said Patrick Devine, Partner at KKR. &#8220;They have a rare combination of innovation and operational sophistication. We are excited to help them scale to meet the needs of an industry that is hungry for faster, higher-quality outcomes.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As of May 2026, Reserv serves nearly 200 clients, including major insurers, managing general agents (MGAs), and corporate captives. With this latest round, Reserv is positioned not just as a technology provider but as the primary infrastructure for the future of global claims handling.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/reserv-raises-125m-to-transform-insurance-claims/" data-wpel-link="internal">Reserv Raises $125M to Transform Insurance Claims</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
